stories.storyText:
[Code Name] Gitano 
[Gender] Female 
[Combat Experience] 1 year 
[Place of Birth] Sami 
[Date of Birth] Jan. 15 
[Race] Elafia 
[Height] 171cm 
[Infection Status] 
Showed physical signs of Originium, infection confirmed by medical examination.

[Physical Strength] Normal 
[Mobility] Normal 
[Physical Resilience] Normal 
[Tactical Acumen] Standard 
[Combat Skill] Standard 
[Originium Arts Assimilation] Excellent

Gitano is a mystic from Sami, tarot expert and a great card player. She has never spoken to anyone of her past prior coming to Rhodes Island, and it remains a mystery. All anyone knows is that her readings are very accurate.

Imaging tests for this Operator showed blurry outlines of internal organs with visible dark spots. Unusually high concentrations of Originium particles were present in her circulatory system, indicating infection and confirming her as Infected at this stage. 

[Cell-Originium Assimilation] 5% 
The infection could be related to Operator Gitano's arcane abilities, though this has yet been proven.. 

[Blood Originium-Crystal Density] 0.3u/L 
Infection approaching mid-stage, Originium beginning to have physical effects that are not obvious.

A fortune teller cannot tell her own future, but she can read the omens and guide her choices. She has the power to create devastating explosions with her Originium crystal ball, but she must also withstand the backlash.

Divination is a hobby to Gitano that she does almost for free, accepting fruits and cakes as a token payment. Her clients ask for readings on anything from the future to a misplaced key. Just like any soothsayer, Gitano gives ambiguous answers that require some careful thought to decipher.

Unlike her relaxed composure during a reading, Gitano gets anxious easily and becomes very competitive when playing cards. She is never allowed to shuffle the deck out of fear that she'll cheat. Even then, she knows countless other card tricks, and unless she's caught red-handed, she'll never admit to cheating. Still, some people play with her because they either want to catch her in the act, or see a nervous side of her she doesn't otherwise show.

Custom-made to suit each Operator's experiences and needs, these outfits are designed to provide them maximum flexibility on any battlefield. Furthermore, this is all done without compromising the comfort that they've come to expect.
EPOQUE New Arrivals/Unknown Journey. Trendy, made for the spring season, well-fitting and comfortable, comes with a choice of accessories that can be mixed and matched to suit your style.

modules.desc:
Operator Gitano has demonstrated a remarkable aptitude for inflicting Arts casualties on multitudes of enemies.
The Field Operations Department has thus passed the following resolution:
This operator shall be appointed a Caster Operator during field operations to exercise Splash Caster responsibilities.
In witness whereof,
This badge is hereby conferred upon the above named.

The moment she raises her crystal ball, Gitano foresees danger.
The squad is escorting a group of rescued Infected to Rhodes Island's transport. After the intense battle, everyone is visibly exhausted. She reminds her teammates to watch out for an ambush, but not a moment after she finishes—and before her teammates had time to react—the ambushers have already emerged from behind the boulders.
The very next moment, the fog that clouds the barrenland is immediately split asunder by the blinding flash of Originium Arts, forcing the ambushers to take a step back.
It seems casting the Arts was too much for Gitano to bear, giving her a spell of dizziness and a burning sensation at the source of her infection. 'You can't keep using your Originium Arts like that.' The advice she got from her tribespeople years ago echoes in her ear. 'Your body can't withstand it anymore. You'll fall ill if you keep casting them.'
Nonetheless, she has pushed herself to her limits in the tundra more times than she can count. With the responsibilities she shoulders, she's never been one to fear falling ill.
Some time later, she faintly overhears two men talking in hushed voices.
'Shh—It's okay. She fell asleep because she's tired. Her infection hasn't gotten worse. Don't worry.'
'We have her to thank for reacting so quickly, otherwise we wouldn't have made it back in one piece.'
'How did she foresee the ambush, though? If she's really able to peek into the future, wouldn't she also know that—'
'Don't be stupid. She herself often says that destiny is something that can be changed.'
'Will you really resist the guidance of fate itself?' All those years ago, her tribespeople implored her. 'We need to turn around. We don't want to leave our homeland, and we've already paid a dear price.'
But the young fortune teller kept leading them onward.

The Rhodes Island transport pulls out of the site with the team, after their successful rescue mission. The Elafia holds tightly onto her crystal ball as she sleeps on the stretcher. She dreams of the black forest back home and the bitter, salty snowdrops, as well as the silhouettes of the mountain chains peeking above the horizon. She's never turned around, nor can she ever go back.

voice_lines.voiceText: Alright, Doctor, your tarot card for today is...
Would you like to learn more about your future?
Bear it in mind that excessive reliance on unfathomed power will eventually backfire on us.
Tarot cards aren't divine, all-seeing tools. Instead, we use them for guidance when we feel lost.
Destiny is like the world we walk upon—no one can escape it.
Humans might never be able to escape this world... but we can change it. Our actions belie endless possibilities.
There are countless topics for which you can consult the tarot, the most common one being your luck in card games. To change it, however, you must be brave enough to change your fate first.
We have a ritual among diviners that's all the rage these days. We call it the 'Hand of Fate.' Would you like to try it?
It's a divination taboo to do readings concerning death. But I don't believe death is the end—it's the beginning of something new.
Dreams can often enlighten you in strange ways. If you have an enlightening dream like that, you'd best remember every detail, Doctor.
Following the guidance of the arcana, our paths have finally converged. Nice to meet you, Doctor.
I feel inspired now.
I'd already foreseen this promotion in my crystal ball. Heheh, just kidding.
You want to know your destiny, Doctor? Too bad, I can't help you. I'm not the one to share it with you, for the fate forbids me to do so.
Wait a minute, let me predict the results of this battle.
Well then, let me pray for everyone.
Fate is a fickle thing... only the victorious will be forever revered.
I can see the outcome. Victory belongs to Rhodes Island.
A very wise choice.
My turn.
Draw a card.
Do not resist your fate.
The tower of void.
The flying chariot.
The Emperor's scepter shall break.
All will fall before the Priestess's might.
Will fate have us in a chokehold… or will we turn the table?
I have moved all of them to the graveyard.
Time to reshuffle the deck.
Impossible... this isn't what I saw in the cards...
Bad omens seem to lurk inside this room. May I use my powers to help you manage them?
Hm? What can I do for you?
Want me to do a reading on your future? All right, please give me a minute.
Arknights.

Happy new year, Doctor. I bet you are eager to learn your fortune this year from me, aren't you? I have, truth be told, stolen a peek into it. My divination was reliable, as always. Still, only by unveiling the fate's mask with your own hands will you discover what lies beneath, don't you agree? No need to worry, I will be there to help you.
Doctor, you're blessed by the winds of luck.

Happy birthday, Doctor. As my birthday gift for you, I will answer any one question from you about the future. Yes, anything will be fine. I would like to remind you though, that I don't offer this knid of chance everyday, so think twice before you ask.

There's no preordained path where one shall walk, nor predestined fate which one shall suffer. And everyone on Rhodes Island has proved that many, many times. Here, Doctor, Peek into the crystall ball. As long as your heart is not shadowed by the clouds, you will see the light of hope at the end of the haze.
